// Task scheduler can be used to create timers to trigger periodically. A
// service can be attached to the task Scheduler object using `attach()`
// function, and the listener can be started using `start()` function.
// Attaching service must contain `onTrigger()` resource function. A parameter
// can be passed into the service using the defaultable parameter `attachment`
// through the `attach()` function, which is passed to the `onTrigger()`
// function. Listener can be stopped by calling `stop()` function.
